example.ex: The Workers' Party failed to win a single governorship...
example.tran: 劳工党连一个州长职位也未能赢得。

example.ex: He failed in his attempt to take control of the company...
example.tran: 他试图掌控公司，但以失败告终。

example.ex: Many of us have tried to lose weight and failed miserably...
example.tran: 我们中很多人都努力要减肥，无奈均以惨败告终。

example.ex: The truth is, I'm a failed comedy writer really.
example.tran: 事实上，我真的是个很失败的喜剧作家。

value.def: If you fail to do something that you were trying to do, you are unable to do it or do not succeed in doing it.

example.ex: We tried to develop plans for them to get along, which all failed miserably...
example.tran: 我们试图计划让他们好好相处，但均以惨败告终。

example.ex: He was afraid the revolution they had started would fail...
example.tran: 他担心他们发起的大变革会遭遇失败。

example.ex: After a failed military offensive, all government troops and police were withdrawn from the island.
example.tran: 在一次军事进攻失败之后，所有政府军和警察均从岛上撤离了。

value.def: If an activity, attempt, or plan fails, it is not successful.
value.tran: (活动、尝试、计划等)失败，不成功

example.ex: Some schools fail to set any homework...
example.tran: 有些学校没有布置任何作业。

example.ex: He failed to file tax returns for 1982...
example.tran: 他没有呈报 1982 年的纳税申报单。

example.ex: The bomb failed to explode.
example.tran: 炸弹没有爆炸。

value.def: If someone or something fails to do a particular thing that they should have done, they do not do it.

example.ex: The lights mysteriously failed, and we stumbled around in complete darkness...
example.tran: 灯不知怎么地不亮了，我们在一片黑暗中跌跌撞撞地走着。

example.ex: In fact many food crops failed because of the drought.
example.tran: 实际上，因为干旱，很多粮食作物歉收。

value.def: If something fails, it stops working properly, or does not do what it is supposed to do.

example.ex: So far this year, 104 banks have failed.
example.tran: 今年到目前为止，已有 104 家银行倒闭。

example.ex: ...a failed hotel business...
example.tran: 破产的酒店

example.ex: Who wants to buy a computer from a failing company?
example.tran: 谁愿意从一家要倒闭的公司买计算机呢？

value.def: If a business, organization, or system fails, it becomes unable to continue in operation or in existence.
value.tran: (企业)倒闭，破产;(机构)解体;(体系)崩溃

example.ex: He was 58, and his health was failing rapidly...
example.tran: 他 58 岁，身体正在迅速衰老。

example.ex: Here in the hills, the light failed more quickly...
example.tran: 在山区这儿，天黑得更快。

example.ex: An apparently failing memory is damaging for a national leader.
example.tran: 明显的记忆力衰退对一个国家领导人来说极为不利。

value.def: If something such as your health or a physical quality is failing, it is becoming gradually weaker or less effective.
value.tran: (健康状况、体质等)衰弱，虚弱，衰退

example.ex: We waited twenty-one years, don't fail us now.
example.tran: 我们等了 21 年了，如今不要让我们失望。

example.ex: ...communities who feel that the political system has failed them.
example.tran: 对此套政治体制感到失望的群体

value.def: If someone fails you, they do not do what you had expected or trusted them to do.

example.ex: Lawyers are accused of failing in their duties to advise clients of their rights...
example.tran: 律师们被控未尽到告知当事人其正当权利的职责。

example.ex: If we did not report what was happening in the country, we would be failing in our duty.
example.tran: 如果我们没有报道这个国家正在发生的事情，我们就没有尽到自己的责任。

value.def: If someone fails in their duty or fails in their responsibilities, they do not do everything that they have a duty or a responsibility to do.

example.ex: For once, the artist's fertile imagination failed him...
example.tran: 这位画家丰富的想象力曾一度枯竭。

example.ex: Their courage failed a few steps short and they came running back.
example.tran: 还差几步他们却胆怯了，又跑回来了。

value.def: If a quality or ability that you have fails you, or if it fails, it is not good enough in a particular situation to enable you to do what you want to do.
value.tran: (品质或能力)有负于;(使)不如愿;不够

example.ex: I lived in fear of failing my end-of-term exams.
example.tran: 我总是担心期末考试不及格。

example.ex: It's the difference between a pass and a fail.
example.tran: 这是及格和不及格的差别。

value.def: If someone fails a test, examination, or course, they perform badly in it and do not reach the standard that is required.

example.ex: ...the two men who had failed him during his first year of law school.
example.tran: 在法学院一年级时让他不及格的两个人

value.def: If someone fails you in a test, examination, or course, they judge that you have not reached a high enough standard in it.

example.ex: If all else fails, I could always drive a truck.
example.tran: 如果其他都不行，我总还可以开卡车。

value.def: You say if all else fails to suggest what could be done in a certain situation if all the other things you have tried are unsuccessful.
value.tran: 如果其他一切都不奏效的话;假如其他都行不通

example.ex: That's how it was in my day and I fail to see why it should be different now.
example.tran: 我那时候就是这样的，我搞不懂为什么现在非要弄得不一样。

value.def: You can use I fail to see or I fail to understand in order to introduce a statement which indicates that you do not agree with what someone has said or done.
value.tran: (用以表示不赞成)不明白，看不出

example.ex: He attended every meeting without fail.
example.tran: 他逢会必到。

value.def: You use without fail to emphasize that something always happens.

example.ex: On the 30th you must without fail hand in some money for Alex...
example.tran: 30 日那天你必须替亚历克斯交一些钱。

example.ex: Tomorrow without fail he would be at the old riverside warehouse.
example.tran: 明天他一定会在河边的旧仓库里。

value.def: You use without fail to emphasize an order or a promise.
value.tran: (用以强调命令或承诺)一定，必须
